cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.DC, cs.SI, cs.CY 

The paper discusses self-adaptive authorisation infrastructures, which are related to access control and security. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses software systems and their adaptation, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.SE (Software Engineering). Additionally, the paper discusses the management of access control, which could fall under cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper discusses cost-effectiveness, which could relate to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
